msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:178
msgid ""
"``stdin`` will read from the terminal in command line engines and use "
"``window.prompt()`` in browsers (in both cases, with line buffering)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:179
msgid ""
"``stdout`` will use a ``print`` function if one such is defined, printing to "
"the terminal in command line engines and to the browser console in browsers "
"that have a console (again, line-buffered)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:180
msgid "``stderr`` will use the same output function as ``stdout``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:182
msgid ""
"All the configuration should be done before the ``main()`` is executed, "
"typically by implementing :js:attr:`Module.preRun`. See :ref:`Interacting-"
"with-code` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:187
msgid "Sets up standard I/O devices for ``stdin``, ``stdout``, and ``stderr``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:189
msgid ""
"The devices are set up using the following (optional) callbacks. If any of "
"the callbacks throw an exception, it will be caught and handled as if the "
"device malfunctioned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:191
msgid ""
"Input callback. This will be called with no parameters whenever the program "
"attempts to read from ``stdin``. It should return an ASCII character code "
"when data is available, or ``null`` when it isn't."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:192
msgid ""
"Output callback. This will be called with an ASCII character code whenever "
"the program writes to ``stdout``. It may also be called with ``null`` to "
"flush the output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:193
msgid ""
"Error callback. This is similar to ``output``, except it is called when data "
"is written to ``stderr``."
msgstr ""

