"true }`` would return an object representing ``/foo``. The default is "
"``false``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.rst:931
msgid ""
"**follow** (*bool*) If true, follow the last component if it is a symlink. "
"For example, consider a symlink ``/foo/symlink`` that links to ``/foo/notes."
"txt``. If ``{ follow: true }``, an object representing ``/foo/notes.txt`` "
